# No fix available upstream for these CVEs as of 2026-05-27.
# Each entry should have a corresponding rationale paragraph in
# docs/trivy-rationale.md. The Trivy CI gate runs with
# `ignore-unfixed: true`, so these unfixed-upstream CVEs are
# already filtered out today; this list exists so the day someone
# flips `ignore-unfixed: false` we don't get a wall of failures
# for issues that have no remediation.

# ncurses: buffer overflow (affected, no fix released)
CVE-2025-69720

# libexpat1: integer-overflow info disclosure (affected, no fix released)
CVE-2026-25210
